1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,300
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:02,667
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:06,307 --> 00:00:08,833
That's weird.
Why isn't the emergency button working?

4
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:10,567
(Episode 67)

5
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:14,587
What's wrong, Team Manager?
Is it happening again, like last time?

6
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:16,560
What do we do?

7
00:00:21,660 --> 00:00:22,813
Are you okay, Team Manager?

8
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:25,266
Just hang in there, okay?

9
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,833
Someone... The security camera!

10
00:00:28,593 --> 00:00:31,786
Help! Someone's trapped in here!

11
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:35,420
Help! Someone's trapped in here! Help!

12
00:00:42,973 --> 00:00:43,973
Hang on.

13
00:00:45,867 --> 00:00:46,980
Just stay still.

14
00:00:48,753 --> 00:00:49,753
Please.

15
00:00:51,307 --> 00:00:53,620
What's wrong, Team Manager?

16
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:05,467
(Panic disorder, Claustrophobia)

17
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:11,867
Team Manager!

18
00:01:14,953 --> 00:01:15,953
What's wrong, Team Manager?

19
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:17,553
Is it happening again, like last time?

20
00:01:23,946 --> 00:01:25,993
I think he might have panic disorder.

21
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:30,620
What are you doing?

22
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:32,767
Nothing.

23
00:01:35,180 --> 00:01:37,713
Anyway, you seem different these days.

24
00:01:38,073 --> 00:01:40,546
Me? Different how?

25
00:01:41,706 --> 00:01:44,627
You don't seem like...

26
00:01:44,627 --> 00:01:46,047
the tomboyish Eun Nim I used to know.

27
00:01:46,967 --> 00:01:49,267
You're one to talk.

28
00:01:49,267 --> 00:01:52,653
You're not the engineering geek Eun Ae
you used to be either.

29
00:01:56,573 --> 00:01:58,746
Come out to the yard. Let's rehearse.

30
00:01:59,966 --> 00:02:01,500
Why would we rehearse in the yard?

31
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,033
Team Manager wants you outside?

32
00:02:04,393 --> 00:02:06,220
What are you two thinking?

33
00:02:06,740 --> 00:02:09,340
Didn't I tell you to stop worrying
for nothing?

34
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:13,853
All right, we're recording now.

35
00:02:13,986 --> 00:02:15,953
You're actually recording this?
Now I'm nervous.

36
00:02:16,413 --> 00:02:19,546
You need to watch yourself present...

37
00:02:19,547 --> 00:02:21,147
to see your strengths and weaknesses.

38
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:24,686
Ready, cue.

39
00:02:25,841 --> 00:02:26,841
Hello.

40
00:02:26,841 --> 00:02:29,993
I'm Cho Eun Ae, an intern on TF Team Two.

41
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:33,085
Today I'll be explaining
how Joy will be used...

42
00:02:33,085 --> 00:02:35,512
in Our Happy Home...

43
00:02:36,973 --> 00:02:38,439
Cut. No good.

44
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:41,480
Eun Ae,
why are you so conscious of the camera?

45
00:02:41,747 --> 00:02:43,927
Look at me. Pretend I'm one of the judges.

46
00:02:44,193 --> 00:02:45,253
Look me in the eye.

47
00:02:46,220 --> 00:02:47,220
Look you in the eye?

48
00:02:48,013 --> 00:02:50,120
That sounds familiar.

49
00:02:51,047 --> 00:02:52,366
Are you ready?

50
00:02:52,766 --> 00:02:54,846
Ready, action.

51
00:02:55,613 --> 00:02:57,513
What is this, a movie?

52
00:02:58,327 --> 00:02:59,327
Focus.

53
00:03:00,966 --> 00:03:02,066
Good grief.

54
00:03:04,566 --> 00:03:06,566
What's wrong? Did something happen?

55
00:03:06,947 --> 00:03:08,853
It's about Team Manager Ko and Eun Ae.

56
00:03:09,753 --> 00:03:13,873
You should be the one to talk to Eun Ae.

57
00:03:15,486 --> 00:03:19,220
She'll take it better from you
than from me.

58
00:03:19,293 --> 00:03:20,693
She won't be as hurt.

59
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:24,820
In the end, because of me, Eun Ae too...

60
00:03:26,913 --> 00:03:27,913
Honey.

61
00:03:28,773 --> 00:03:31,600
Team Manager Ko is adopted.

62
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,466
What?

63
00:03:35,693 --> 00:03:39,493
The Chairman adopted him from an orphanage
when he was seven...

64
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:42,027
and raised him as CEO Ko's son.

65
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:47,053
The Chairman isn't related to you by blood
and the same goes for Team Manager Ko.

66
00:03:47,793 --> 00:03:50,026
Do you really have to force
those two apart?

67
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:51,880
How...

68
00:03:52,773 --> 00:03:54,760
How could Team Manager Ko...

69
00:03:55,687 --> 00:03:57,587
There's still time left on his contract,

70
00:03:57,587 --> 00:03:59,447
and he's swamped
preparing for the competition.

71
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:03,900
Let's not make things harder
by telling him to move out or break up.

72
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:10,366
And wouldn't you consider...

73
00:04:11,073 --> 00:04:12,900
talking to your mother calmly?

74
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:15,200
You should at least hear her side.

75
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,560
There you go again.

76
00:04:17,313 --> 00:04:20,340
Fine. Let's just go to bed.

77
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:29,413
So, did everything go well?
Did you secure the files?

78
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:32,840
Don't worry about that.

79
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:36,199
I'll handle the security office...

80
00:04:36,199 --> 00:04:37,752
and machine room staff myself.

81
00:04:39,473 --> 00:04:40,686
All right, I'll hang up.

82
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:45,426
What do you mean,
you'll handle it yourself?

83
00:04:46,913 --> 00:04:47,913
The less you know, the better.

84
00:04:49,046 --> 00:04:51,399
Right, I talked to Seong Jun today.

85
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,505
He says they're not interested...

86
00:04:53,506 --> 00:04:55,019
in shares or family registration.

87
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:59,206
Maybe Mr. Cho isn't,
but Kang Yeon Ja is a different story.

88
00:04:59,546 --> 00:05:02,453
She may be too resentful to see it now,

89
00:05:02,653 --> 00:05:04,113
but do you really think
she won't get greedy?

90
00:05:04,719 --> 00:05:06,800
There's a reason they say
seeing something makes you want it.

91
00:05:07,827 --> 00:05:10,140
Crystal, do you even know that saying?

92
00:05:11,066 --> 00:05:12,520
What do you take me for?

93
00:05:12,759 --> 00:05:14,940
Even a dog gets greedy
when it sees something it wants.

94
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:17,280
Dog and things.

95
00:05:17,766 --> 00:05:20,806
Well, it's not about dogs wanting things.

96
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:22,367
All right, let's stop here.

97
00:05:22,707 --> 00:05:24,659
I have the second round tomorrow,

98
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:26,460
so I need to be well-rested.

99
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,766
I'll be swamped tomorrow too.

100
00:05:31,266 --> 00:05:32,266
What are you going to be busy with?

101
00:05:33,347 --> 00:05:34,447
The less you know, the better.

102
00:05:34,867 --> 00:05:36,567
I have my own plans too.

103
00:05:39,159 --> 00:05:41,559
(Kangsu Construction)

104
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:44,580
(Kangsu Construction
Retirement Community Project, Round Two)

105
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:50,100
(TF Team Two)

106
00:05:50,598 --> 00:05:51,825
Pass this on to Mr. Han Ji Hun.

107
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,067
(TF Team Two)

108
00:06:01,033 --> 00:06:02,033
You can do this, right?

109
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:05,893
I wasn't even this nervous
at Lucky Joy's investor presentation.

110
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,160
Why am I so nervous?

111
00:06:11,313 --> 00:06:12,873
Here. Your lucky charm.

112
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:18,767
Thank you, Team Manager.

113
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,073
We're all set.

114
00:06:21,367 --> 00:06:23,267
Team Manager, Ms. Cho, let's do this!

115
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:24,620
Let's do this!

116
00:06:42,820 --> 00:06:43,820
The Chairman has arrived.

117
00:07:07,187 --> 00:07:08,780
Let's begin.

118
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,153
Before we start the second round,

119
00:07:14,626 --> 00:07:16,966
I'd like to introduce our guest judges.

120
00:07:17,266 --> 00:07:19,793
During the first round,

121
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:23,313
I noticed the guest judges were very fair.

122
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:37,433
Chairman, have the guest judges changed?

123
00:07:37,846 --> 00:07:39,913
The evaluation criteria
are different this round.

124
00:07:40,747 --> 00:07:42,613
Naturally, the judges changed too.

125
00:07:43,186 --> 00:07:48,253
I'm Erich Baumann, an operations expert
in smart retirement communities.

126
00:07:48,886 --> 00:07:52,592
I'll focus on the integration of AI...

127
00:07:52,593 --> 00:07:55,826
with the retirement community
and its sustainability.

128
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:58,853
I'm Choi Gi Ryong,
CEO of a senior infrastructure asset firm.

129
00:07:59,426 --> 00:08:03,686
I'll evaluate investment return potential
and market scalability.

130
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:07,006
I am AN, an AI system that analyzes...

131
00:08:07,007 --> 00:08:09,040
compatibility between humans
and their environment.

132
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:14,180
I'll evaluate AI implementation
and AI ethics.

133
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:52,240
What could have happened...

134
00:08:52,827 --> 00:08:55,240
for Team Manager Ko
to end up in an orphanage?

135
00:08:56,413 --> 00:09:00,393
Seven is when a child
needs their parents the most.

136
00:09:05,726 --> 00:09:07,086
What brings you here this time?

137
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:10,333
Don't you think we need to talk?

138
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:28,886
My husband told me...

139
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:32,025
that Mr. Cho said
he has absolutely no intention...

140
00:09:32,026 --> 00:09:34,493
of becoming part of our family.

141
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:36,626
What about you?

142
00:09:37,220 --> 00:09:38,813
What are you trying to say?

143
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:42,326
Are you implying I'm after the position...

144
00:09:42,734 --> 00:09:44,080
of the Chairman's daughter?

145
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,113
Then aren't you?

146
00:09:45,547 --> 00:09:48,186
You're about to become Kangsu Group's
chairman's daughter overnight.

147
00:09:49,886 --> 00:09:52,146
Of course you'll get greedy.

148
00:09:53,619 --> 00:09:54,679
Listen, Min Ho's mom.

149
00:09:55,613 --> 00:09:57,252
Are you really asking for trouble?

150
00:09:57,253 --> 00:09:58,720
What? Trouble?

151
00:09:59,919 --> 00:10:02,600
Are you saying
you're going to grab me by the hair?

152
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:05,220
You grabbed mine. Why can't I grab yours?

153
00:10:05,686 --> 00:10:09,480
Come to think of it, you already knew
who I was back then, didn't you?

154
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,420
You pulled my hair for a DNA test, right?

155
00:10:12,613 --> 00:10:13,613
Of course.

156
00:10:14,093 --> 00:10:15,919
When a birth secret comes out
in a wealthy family,

157
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:19,060
a DNA test is practically mandatory.

158
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:22,740
Min Ho's mom... No, Ms. Eun Su Jeong.

159
00:10:23,087 --> 00:10:26,127
I have no interest in being part
of a wealthy family or anything like that.

160
00:10:27,967 --> 00:10:29,553
You're clearly not someone
I can reason with.

161
00:10:29,753 --> 00:10:31,686
Just go. Leave!

162
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:37,079
This is why you should never associate
with people with no background.

163
00:10:38,946 --> 00:10:41,173
Kang Yeon Ja, do you even know who I am?

164
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:44,240
I'm your sister-in-law.

165
00:10:44,713 --> 00:10:47,139
How dare you speak
to your elder like that?

166
00:10:47,246 --> 00:10:48,413
What? Sister-in-law?

167
00:10:49,453 --> 00:10:50,453
Get out.

168
00:10:50,553 --> 00:10:52,393
- Get out!
- Wait.

169
00:10:53,646 --> 00:10:55,853
Then promise me one thing.

170
00:10:56,733 --> 00:10:58,873
Don't ever register yourself
in our family registry...

171
00:10:59,113 --> 00:11:01,813
or lay a finger on Kangsu Group's shares.

172
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:05,206
Then I'll buy you...
Maybe a five-story building?

173
00:11:05,406 --> 00:11:08,159
No, a ten-story one.

174
00:11:08,813 --> 00:11:11,132
I'll make you a building owner.

175
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:12,573
You!

176
00:11:15,053 --> 00:11:18,566
Want me to soak you in salt water...

177
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:20,253
like you were napa cabbage?

178
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:23,639
Seriously,
what is wrong with people around here?

179
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:25,359
Is this place cursed or something?

180
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:26,813
Unbelievable.

181
00:11:27,233 --> 00:11:28,506
How classless.

182
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:35,826
A ten-story building, my foot.

183
00:11:36,253 --> 00:11:39,353
Look at her. What a piece of work.

184
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,000
(Our Happy Home)

185
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,606
The ultimate goal of Our Happy Home...

186
00:11:43,020 --> 00:11:44,627
isn't a place
where people stay temporarily.

187
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,833
It's a home where they want to live
for the rest of their lives,

188
00:11:47,193 --> 00:11:49,520
a true community.

189
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:53,420
As relationships and bonds grow stronger,

190
00:11:53,846 --> 00:11:55,380
more people will choose to stay long-term.

191
00:11:55,827 --> 00:11:58,107
And when that happens,

192
00:11:58,307 --> 00:12:00,287
the project's profitability
will naturally follow.

193
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:03,127
Where people choose to stay,

194
00:12:03,906 --> 00:12:06,419
a sustainable future follows.

195
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:09,546
Next,
the software integration presentation...

196
00:12:09,926 --> 00:12:13,693
will be given by Joy's developer,
intern Cho Eun Ae.

197
00:12:35,533 --> 00:12:36,680
Hello.

198
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:39,673
I'm Cho Eun Ae, an intern
on the Retirement Community TF Team Two.

199
00:12:39,886 --> 00:12:41,153
I'll begin my presentation.

200
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:49,800
What's going on?

201
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:50,800
I think it's the wrong file.

202
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:52,500
Why is that on the screen?

203
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:55,467
It looks like a technical issue.

204
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:56,900
- What's wrong with him?
- He looks sick.

205
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:57,900
Who is that?

206
00:12:57,900 --> 00:12:58,900
(Our Happy Home)

207
00:13:01,327 --> 00:13:02,327
What is that?

208
00:13:03,133 --> 00:13:04,593
Is it a playback error?

209
00:13:04,886 --> 00:13:06,720
Isn't that Team Manager Ko?

210
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,866
Doesn't he look unwell?

211
00:13:13,153 --> 00:13:14,153
He does.

212
00:13:15,020 --> 00:13:16,380
He looks sick.

213
00:13:16,733 --> 00:13:18,233
What do you mean?

214
00:13:18,599 --> 00:13:20,292
Are you saying the team leader
who'll be in charge...

215
00:13:20,293 --> 00:13:22,926
of a project worth hundreds
of millions of dollars is unwell?

216
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,200
Enough.

217
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:28,739
Why all the commotion
over a technical glitch?

218
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:33,093
Chairman,
it's not just a technical glitch.

219
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:35,953
Team Manager Ko doesn't look well.

220
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:44,246
I'll hold those responsible...

221
00:13:45,393 --> 00:13:48,126
for the playback error
after the competition is over.

222
00:13:49,613 --> 00:13:50,613
Continue the presentation.

223
00:13:59,946 --> 00:14:02,840
First of all, I'd like to apologize.

224
00:14:03,926 --> 00:14:07,326
Team Manager Ko and I
are currently dating.

225
00:14:07,839 --> 00:14:10,353
Yesterday, while working late
to prepare for the competition,

226
00:14:10,633 --> 00:14:13,039
we were involved
in an unexpected elevator accident.

227
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:16,180
I don't know how this video
ended up being played,

228
00:14:16,820 --> 00:14:20,559
but we've unintentionally gone public
with our relationship.

229
00:14:21,673 --> 00:14:25,693
Could it be that someone
deliberately leaked it?

230
00:14:47,513 --> 00:14:50,333
Now, let me introduce...

231
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:51,826
Joy from Our Happy Home.

232
00:14:54,873 --> 00:14:56,146
Seriously.

233
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:05,500
Mr. Han Ji Hun.

234
00:15:06,427 --> 00:15:08,873
Yes, Manager. I'll be right in.

235
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:11,413
No, there's no need to come in.

236
00:15:12,926 --> 00:15:15,393
Excuse me?
I'm about to give the presentation.

237
00:15:15,813 --> 00:15:18,013
You're no longer qualified to present.

238
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:19,700
Go wait for your disciplinary action.

239
00:15:20,786 --> 00:15:22,899
- Excuse me?
- I'll be giving today's presentation.

240
00:15:24,627 --> 00:15:25,646
Manager.

241
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,100
(Major Cultural Facilities)

242
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,606
Joy from Our Happy Home is your friend.

243
00:15:35,766 --> 00:15:39,493
The air's fresh today,
and it's perfect for a walk.

244
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:43,438
Today, Building G and Building N...

245
00:15:43,439 --> 00:15:44,746
have a chess match scheduled.

246
00:15:45,060 --> 00:15:47,360
Why not go out and cheer them on?

247
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:50,753
Your waltz club meets at 7 p.m.

248
00:15:51,587 --> 00:15:55,080
The blue dress you wore last time
looked lovely,

249
00:15:55,387 --> 00:15:58,233
but today, I recommend the floral one.

250
00:16:00,867 --> 00:16:01,920
That's how Joy...

251
00:16:03,193 --> 00:16:05,240
helps every resident
become one happy family...

252
00:16:05,393 --> 00:16:09,220
and enjoy every day together.

253
00:16:16,146 --> 00:16:18,140
Our sports robot uses AI...

254
00:16:18,313 --> 00:16:21,240
to analyze the user's health
and athletic ability...

255
00:16:21,867 --> 00:16:23,700
and provide customized gameplay.

256
00:16:24,286 --> 00:16:26,413
We're currently in development talks...

257
00:16:26,773 --> 00:16:29,573
with the humanoid robotics company,
Hubridge Robotics.

258
00:16:32,146 --> 00:16:33,619
Team One's Joy...

259
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:34,919
(AI Emotional Care Assistant, Joy)

260
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:36,253
is the perfect assistant.

261
00:16:37,687 --> 00:16:39,040
It remembers the user's daily life,

262
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,640
notices the slightest emotional changes,

263
00:16:42,407 --> 00:16:45,580
and stands by the user's side
with empathy and support.

264
00:16:46,253 --> 00:16:50,120
There's no need to wait for a call
or get hurt by relationships.

265
00:16:57,773 --> 00:16:59,740
Everyone else's mom will be there.

266
00:17:00,806 --> 00:17:03,773
What if Bit Na is disappointed
because her grandma came instead?

267
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:10,100
Yeon Sun.

268
00:17:13,233 --> 00:17:15,733
Why on earth did you come here again?

269
00:17:16,266 --> 00:17:18,699
Wasn't I clear enough the last time?

270
00:17:19,233 --> 00:17:20,267
I'm sorry.

271
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,607
I just wanted to see you,
so I stopped by for a moment.

272
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:27,260
I was just about to leave these here.

273
00:17:29,933 --> 00:17:31,273
Didn't I tell you before?

274
00:17:32,453 --> 00:17:36,246
When I was little, I threw up
after eating the flower pancakes you made.

275
00:17:37,079 --> 00:17:39,113
Do you really think...

276
00:17:39,306 --> 00:17:40,880
I could stomach the food you've brought?

277
00:17:41,567 --> 00:17:43,446
I know, but...

278
00:17:45,547 --> 00:17:46,547
But even if it's late,

279
00:17:47,826 --> 00:17:49,893
I wanted to make up for...

280
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:52,960
all the things I couldn't do for you
over the past 50 years.

281
00:17:54,579 --> 00:17:55,813
Can't you try...

282
00:17:57,419 --> 00:17:59,193
to understand how your mother feels?

283
00:17:59,353 --> 00:18:00,353
Why should I?

284
00:18:00,853 --> 00:18:03,466
Why should I be the one to understand?
Why?

285
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:08,506
My goodness, what do we do?

286
00:18:09,093 --> 00:18:12,826
Yeon Ja was already furious
this morning...

287
00:18:12,827 --> 00:18:15,993
because of Madam's daughter-in-law,
and now she's upset again.

288
00:18:16,466 --> 00:18:17,673
- Goodness gracious.
- What?

289
00:18:18,133 --> 00:18:20,733
The Chairman's daughter-in-law
came by today?

290
00:18:20,773 --> 00:18:21,773
Yes.

291
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:25,013
I can already imagine how it went.

292
00:18:25,613 --> 00:18:27,013
Please take these back with you. Hurry.

293
00:18:28,013 --> 00:18:29,873
All right, I'll go.

294
00:18:32,113 --> 00:18:33,866
I'm sorry for making things
so hard on you.

295
00:18:34,967 --> 00:18:37,053
But please accept this food.

296
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:41,213
I know I don't deserve to ask, but...

297
00:18:42,087 --> 00:18:44,513
I hope at least my son-in-law
and grandchildren can eat it.

298
00:18:45,547 --> 00:18:47,080
Your son-in-law and grandchildren?

299
00:18:47,607 --> 00:18:49,013
I'll get going.

300
00:18:57,106 --> 00:18:58,419
Why is she doing this?

301
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:00,832
Why did she show up...

302
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:03,240
and bother someone
who's finally found some peace?

303
00:19:03,646 --> 00:19:06,833
I said I didn't need a mom anymore!

304
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:14,566
Tell me the truth!

305
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:17,500
That's unfair.

306
00:19:18,233 --> 00:19:20,486
How can you accuse me without any proof?

307
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:22,800
Ko Dae Chi!

308
00:19:25,947 --> 00:19:27,139
The Chairman's inside, isn't he?

309
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:30,560
If it wasn't you, then was it Min Ho?

310
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,712
No. Min Ho has been competing...

311
00:19:34,713 --> 00:19:36,199
fair and square in this competition.

312
00:19:36,693 --> 00:19:37,793
It definitely wasn't Min Ho.

313
00:19:40,507 --> 00:19:42,320
Why on earth are you doing this?

314
00:19:42,980 --> 00:19:45,647
Why do you still not understand
why I made you compete?

315
00:19:46,419 --> 00:19:48,333
This is all because of you, Father.

316
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:51,067
From the time I was little until now,

317
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:54,000
I can't even stand up straight
in front of you.

318
00:19:55,073 --> 00:19:57,813
Have I ever once been allowed
to do things my way?

319
00:19:58,573 --> 00:19:59,573
What?

320
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:03,893
Have you ever acknowledged me even once?

321
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:07,579
You've always treated me
like I wasn't good enough.

322
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:09,565
No matter what it takes,
this competition...

323
00:20:09,566 --> 00:20:12,653
So if Min Ho wins, you win too?

324
00:20:14,153 --> 00:20:17,980
This race is about fairness.

325
00:20:18,413 --> 00:20:20,766
That's what I told you...

326
00:20:22,486 --> 00:20:23,586
Father!

327
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:26,367
Fa...

328
00:20:26,367 --> 00:20:28,173
- Chairman!
- Chairman, are you all right?

329
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:29,800
Let's get you to the hospital.

330
00:20:31,486 --> 00:20:33,906
No, I'm fine. I...

331
00:20:34,493 --> 00:20:35,933
I want to go home.

332
00:20:36,066 --> 00:20:38,633
Yes, I'll have the car ready immediately.

333
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,440
Where have you been, Mother?

334
00:20:58,767 --> 00:21:00,600
Please get some rest, Madam.

335
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:04,373
Why is she glaring at me like that?

336
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:07,406
Why did you do that?

337
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:10,346
Why did you have to go over there
and stir things up?

338
00:21:10,526 --> 00:21:11,880
Seriously.

339
00:21:14,139 --> 00:21:16,679
Did she run straight to her mom
and tell on me already?

340
00:21:18,466 --> 00:21:19,466
Honestly.

341
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:23,107
And what brings you here?

342
00:21:23,406 --> 00:21:26,039
I came to see Madam. Is she inside?

343
00:21:26,147 --> 00:21:27,827
Why do you need to see Mother?

344
00:21:27,913 --> 00:21:30,260
Now that Kang Yeon Ja
turned out to be Madam's daughter,

345
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:32,660
I guess you're feeling pretty upset.

346
00:21:33,260 --> 00:21:34,986
Don't you think
you're going a little too far?

347
00:21:37,267 --> 00:21:39,267
Right. I have something to tell you.

348
00:21:39,473 --> 00:21:40,473
Come with me.

349
00:21:40,527 --> 00:21:41,647
What's this about?

350
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,233
Come here!

351
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:50,493
What? Seung Ri was at a hotel with Min Ho?

352
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:53,746
No, that can't be true.

353
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:55,826
She did stay out that night,

354
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:57,739
but she said she stayed
at a friend's house.

355
00:21:58,060 --> 00:21:59,407
What? She stayed out overnight?

356
00:22:01,007 --> 00:22:03,307
I had my suspicions, but it's true.

357
00:22:04,553 --> 00:22:07,446
I didn't think Seung Ri had it in her.
She's pretty sly.

358
00:22:07,573 --> 00:22:08,673
What did you just say?

359
00:22:09,253 --> 00:22:12,033
She made it crystal clear
that she couldn't stand Min Ho,

360
00:22:12,326 --> 00:22:13,453
so what's this new scheme?

361
00:22:13,573 --> 00:22:15,885
Watch it. A scheme?

362
00:22:15,886 --> 00:22:17,253
What? "Watch it?"

363
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,047
Are you picking a fight with me?

364
00:22:20,153 --> 00:22:23,693
Unless I hear it directly
from Seung Ri herself,

365
00:22:24,286 --> 00:22:26,620
I'm not believing a word of it.

366
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:29,407
Hear it from her? It's obvious.

367
00:22:29,820 --> 00:22:31,819
Now that she knows
Gyeol is completely out of reach,

368
00:22:31,820 --> 00:22:34,386
she's settling for Min Ho instead.

369
00:22:34,647 --> 00:22:36,080
Not a chance.

370
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:45,653
What are you trying to do?
Don't tell me...

371
00:22:46,233 --> 00:22:48,593
No! Not my hair!

372
00:22:50,846 --> 00:22:54,320
If it turns out you're wrong
after I check, you'll regret it.

373
00:23:00,433 --> 00:23:01,433
She scared me.

374
00:23:02,053 --> 00:23:04,626
Why's everyone so vicious today?

375
00:23:04,993 --> 00:23:07,633
I can't live like this. How scary.

376
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:10,346
Eun Ae, you were amazing today.

377
00:23:10,827 --> 00:23:12,947
That was the best I've ever seen you.

378
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,573
It's all thanks to you, Team Manager.

379
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:20,199
Your project came from your sincere desire
to build a truly wonderful home,

380
00:23:20,767 --> 00:23:23,279
so I was able to present it sincerely too.

381
00:23:23,926 --> 00:23:26,166
Well,
we still have to wait for the results.

382
00:23:26,540 --> 00:23:28,953
Why are you being so polite and humble?

383
00:23:29,093 --> 00:23:30,093
You're not acting like yourself.

384
00:23:31,173 --> 00:23:32,173
Team Manager,

385
00:23:32,953 --> 00:23:36,253
do you happen to have panic disorder?

386
00:23:38,113 --> 00:23:39,113
What?

387
00:23:40,353 --> 00:23:43,153
The car accident before,
and yesterday's elevator too...

388
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,040
It was all because of that, wasn't it?

389
00:23:45,766 --> 00:23:46,766
No?

390
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:51,200
Have you tried getting treatment?

391
00:23:51,367 --> 00:23:53,699
It's not serious enough to need treatment.

392
00:23:54,166 --> 00:23:57,706
It's just an old childhood nightmare
that came back.

393
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,779
It's really nothing.

394
00:24:01,779 --> 00:24:03,485
Why do you look so worried?

395
00:24:04,513 --> 00:24:06,699
I think someone knew
about your panic disorder...

396
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:10,260
and planned what happened today.
How can I not worry?

397
00:24:11,367 --> 00:24:14,080
If you don't want to go
to the hospital alone, I'll go with you.

398
00:24:14,467 --> 00:24:16,640
Why would I go to the hospital
just because I had a nightmare?

399
00:24:16,893 --> 00:24:18,126
I'm telling you, it's nothing.

400
00:24:19,613 --> 00:24:20,613
Wait a second.

401
00:24:26,053 --> 00:24:27,053
Hello, Grandpa.

402
00:24:27,987 --> 00:24:30,660
It was Mom Participation Day.
Were you disappointed that I came instead?

403
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:33,813
No. Thank you for coming.

404
00:24:36,373 --> 00:24:37,413
Bit Na.

405
00:24:40,453 --> 00:24:41,453
Bit Na.

406
00:24:41,453 --> 00:24:43,053
Mom!

407
00:24:44,333 --> 00:24:45,740
Have you been doing well, Bit Na?

408
00:24:48,460 --> 00:24:49,520
I'm sorry.

409
00:24:50,006 --> 00:24:53,166
I really tried to make it
to your Mom Participation Day class,

410
00:24:54,107 --> 00:24:56,087
but I just couldn't make the time work.

411
00:24:57,313 --> 00:24:58,759
Did you go with Grandma today?

412
00:24:59,453 --> 00:25:01,286
No, with Auntie Cho Rong.

413
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:03,667
Hello.

414
00:25:05,340 --> 00:25:07,707
What happened?
How did you end up going there?

415
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:11,373
Mother had a guest over and couldn't go,

416
00:25:11,567 --> 00:25:12,867
so I went in her place.

417
00:25:14,380 --> 00:25:15,627
Anyway, thank you.

418
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:17,467
Ji Seon.

419
00:25:20,266 --> 00:25:21,266
Hey.

420
00:25:22,466 --> 00:25:23,599
Thank you so much for coming.

421
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,267
Eun Hyeong.

422
00:25:29,300 --> 00:25:31,633
Hey, you're here!

423
00:25:32,833 --> 00:25:34,400
What are you doing?
Don't just stand there.

424
00:25:34,673 --> 00:25:36,420
Come inside and talk.

425
00:25:36,873 --> 00:25:39,673
I'm going to be at the real estate office,
so don't worry about me, okay?

426
00:25:40,113 --> 00:25:41,786
Yes, let's do that, Ji Seon.

427
00:25:42,913 --> 00:25:44,013
Come on in.

428
00:25:47,866 --> 00:25:49,400
Is this the room you and Dad are using,
Bit Na?

429
00:25:50,067 --> 00:25:52,800
No, this is Dad and Uncle Gyeol's room.

430
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:55,340
I sleep in Grandma's room.

431
00:25:55,593 --> 00:25:58,246
When Uncle Gyeol isn't here,
I sleep here with Dad.

432
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:01,420
Uncle Gyeol is...

433
00:26:01,779 --> 00:26:04,746
this room's tenant,
and he's Eun Ae's team manager.

434
00:26:06,806 --> 00:26:10,379
So the two of you
don't have a room of your own.

435
00:26:11,827 --> 00:26:13,673
I'm sorry, Bit Na. It's my fault.

436
00:26:14,133 --> 00:26:15,853
It's okay if I don't have my own room.

437
00:26:16,319 --> 00:26:19,086
So, Mom, don't work too hard.

438
00:26:19,533 --> 00:26:21,073
And Dad, don't get sick.

439
00:26:23,046 --> 00:26:24,046
Are you sick?

440
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:26,180
No, it's not like that.

441
00:26:27,147 --> 00:26:29,946
My shoulder and back hurt a little
after my morning part-time job,

442
00:26:29,947 --> 00:26:33,287
so I put on some pain patches.
I guess she got worried when she saw them.

443
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:36,559
Bit Na, I'm totally fine now. Really.

444
00:26:39,573 --> 00:26:40,733
This is for you.

445
00:26:42,067 --> 00:26:43,067
A present?

446
00:26:43,467 --> 00:26:44,867
It's a kids' phone.

447
00:26:45,460 --> 00:26:48,360
From now on, whenever you miss Mom
or want to tell me something,

448
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:49,960
call me.

449
00:26:50,740 --> 00:26:52,640
I have my own phone now?

450
00:26:52,966 --> 00:26:56,306
Okay. I'll call you all the time
from now on, Mom.

451
00:26:57,340 --> 00:27:01,513
That's my brave girl.
Seeing you doing so well...

452
00:27:01,766 --> 00:27:03,420
makes me so happy.

453
00:27:04,433 --> 00:27:07,012
I may not be able to come often,
but whenever I have time,

454
00:27:07,013 --> 00:27:08,693
I'll come see you. I promise.

455
00:27:09,393 --> 00:27:12,833
Really? You have to keep that promise.

456
00:27:15,567 --> 00:27:16,567
I will.

457
00:27:18,760 --> 00:27:20,260
I promise.

458
00:28:25,167 --> 00:28:26,900
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
